  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Citizens Participation in Local Governance to Improve Accountability in revenue mobilisati</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conduct Rapid assessment in four District Assemblies
Stakeholders engagement and consultation meeting
Formation and Election of Social Accountability Groups for Anti-Corruption Campaigns
Training of Citizens on Social Accountability, Citizen Participation and Popular participation concept. Train active women groups to demand gender sensitive projects
Organizing Social Accountability Platforms (SAP) to build capacity of citizens and promote transparency and good governance at the assembly.
Conduct radio talk-shows to support government decentralization policy issues at the local level
Form and train advocacy groups to engage with Assembly on developmental issues</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Well informed citizens capable of demanding for accountability from public office holders.
Duty Bearers adhering to constitutional provisions on citizen&#x2019;s participation in local governance.
Increased revenue generation by the municipal assembly</narrative>
  </description>
